WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:02.000
How to create a portfolio like mine

00:02.000 --> 00:18.000
Step 1. Login to GitHub.com

00:18.000 --> 00:28.000
Step 2. Enter your GitHub username

00:28.000 --> 00:34.000
Step 3. Go to GitHub.com/new/import

00:34.000 --> 00:43.000
Step 4. Enter the repository url

00:43.000 --> 00:51.000
Step 5. Enter the repository name

00:51.000 --> 01:02.000
Step 6. Click "Begin Import" and then wait for it to complete

01:02.000 --> 01:18.000
Step 7. Edit _data/authors.yml

01:18.000 --> 01:31.000
Step 8. Edit _includes/footer.html

01:31.000 --> 01:47.000
Step 9. Edit _config.yml

01:47.000 --> 02:02.000
Step 10. Edit admin/config.yml

02:02.000 --> 02:15.000
Step 11. Go to Netlify.com and log in with GitHub.

02:15.000 --> 02:26.000
Step 12. Click "New site from Git" and then select GitHub.

02:26.000 --> 02:39.000
Step 13. Select the "YourUsername.github.io" repository and then hit "Deploy Site".

02:39.000 --> 03:04.000
Step 14. Go to Settings -> General -> Site Details and change the site name to "YourUsername".

03:04.000 --> 03:20.000
Step 15. Go to Identity and click "Enable Identity".

03:20.000 --> 03:35.000
Step 16. Go to Settings -> Identity -> Registration and click "Edit settings".

03:35.000 --> 03:44.000
Step 17. Select "Invite only" and then click save.

03:44.000 --> 04:03.000
Step 18. Go to Settings -> Identity -> Services and click "Enable Git Gateway".

04:03.000 --> 04:13.000
Step 19. Go to Identity.

04:13.000 --> 04:41.000
Step 20. Click "Invite users", enter your email, click "Send" and then check your email for a site invitation.

04:41.000 --> 04:46.000
Step 21. Click "Accept the invite" in the email and then enter a password.

04:46.000 --> 04:54.000
Step 22. Go to the admin page (/admin).

04:54.000 --> 05:13.000
Step 23. Login with your email and the password you just created.

05:13.000 --> 05:22.000 
Step 24. Make all of your desired changes using the CMS (Content Management System).

05:22.000 --> 05:32.000 
Step 25. View your site: YourUsername.github.io.